A man has been charged with assaulting his pregnant wife for demanding answers to text messages she found on his phone. Abdul Rezak Rehan is alleged to have kicked Uzma Igbal on the stomach and thighs at Akila lll estate in South C on January 31. The complainant was seven months pregnant. According to a police report in Kibera senior principal magistrate Boaz Ombewa's court, Rehan was questioned by his wife about text messages she suspected were from another woman. He allegedly responded by assaulting her. She shouted for help and was rescued by her family and taken to hospital. Rehan denied the charge through lawyer Okinyo Jabungu, who petitioned the court to free his client on lenient bond terms. Okinyo argued that his client was a family man and a law-abiding citizen. The accused was released on Sh50,000 bond or Sh20,000 bail. The case will be heard on July 8.  - mwaniki fm